  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add chopped onion and bell pepper and cook until tender.",
    "Add fish sauce, nam pla sauce, and coconut cream, and stir to combine.",
    "Add cod fish fillets to the skillet, skin side up.",
    "Cook for 5 minutes, then flip the fish and cook for an additional 5 minutes.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with chopped fresh herbs if desired.",
    "Let the skillet cool before washing to prevent damage.",
    "Store leftovers in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 3 days."
